sentences: Aisha Orazbayeva (Kazakh: AÄ±sha Orazbaeva, born 1985) is a violinist from Kazakhstan.
Orazbayeva collaborated with computer music composer Peter Zinovieff on a violin concerto Our Too, premiered at London Contemporary Music Festival in 2014.
In 2014 composer Bryn Harrison wrote Receiving the Approaching Memory, a 40-minute work for violin and piano, for Orazbayeva and pianist Mark Knoop.
